WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.000
Welcome. In this lesson we connect displacement, velocity, and acceleration for straight-line motion.

00:05.000 --> 00:13.000
Distance is the path length travelled. Displacement is the change in position from start to finish and includes direction.

00:13.000 --> 00:21.000
Average speed uses total distance divided by time. Average velocity uses displacement divided by time.

00:21.000 --> 00:30.000
Acceleration tells how velocity changes with time. Positive and negative signs depend on the chosen direction.

00:30.000 --> 00:39.000
On a position-time graph, slope represents velocity. On a velocity-time graph, slope represents acceleration.

00:39.000 --> 00:48.000
The area under a velocity-time graph gives displacement. Keep units visible in every calculation.

00:48.000 --> 00:55.000
Before you move ahead, test yourself with the article, flashcards, and diagnostic quiz.
